msItem.title: Ya᾿ir nativ (יאיר נתיב)
msItem.author: Ibn al-Gazzar, Aḥmad ibn Ibrahim, 932-1009 (ג'זאר, אחמד בן אבראהים אבן)

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 25; written lines: 25; Uniform layout. Pricking and hard-point ruling visible. Hair side and flesh side of folios hardly distinguishable. Larger initial words. Additions and notes in the margins, partly cut in trimming. Last word of a folio repeated at the beginning of the next. Gilt edges.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Ashkenazi (French?) semi-cursive script of the 14th century.

binding.p: Post-1600. Dark brown leather. Spine: 'Constantinus Africanus. Viaticum. Hebrew. Mus. Brit. Jure Emptionis. 18,969.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Purchased by the British Museum through Asher & Co. on 12 June 1852: inscribed, folio [172v] (fse001v).
